The example of the update function in the Docs uses “set test = ” I think this should be updated to use “do” instead of “set”?

```{% set dict_var = {'authorName': 'Douglas Judy', 'authorTitle': 'Mastermind' } %}
{% set test = dict_var.update({'authorFriend': 'Jake'}) %}
{% set test = dict_var.update({'authorLocation': 'unknown'}) %}
{{ dict_var }}```
```{% set dict_var = {'authorName': 'Douglas Judy', 'authorTitle': 'Mastermind' } %}
{% do dict_var.update({'authorFriend': 'Jake'}) %}
{% do dict_var.update({'authorLocation': 'unknown'}) %}
{{ dict_var }}```
<https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/hubl/functions#update>
